# _pack-skeleton/agents/.keep — copy this pack to .vh-agent-harness/overlays/<pack>/
#
# Drop new agent files here as agents/<name>.md. A pack agent is a normal
# OpenCode subagent prompt with YAML frontmatter; it renders into
# .opencode/agents/<name>.md (ownership overlay_extension) while the pack is
# active. Minimal shape (copy and edit):
#
#   ---
#   description: One line: what this specialist does and when to use it
#   mode: subagent
#   ---
#
#   You are the {{PROJECT_NAME}} <name> specialist.
#
#   - scope: <files/areas this agent owns>
#   - hand off: <what to route elsewhere>
#
# The agent roster + task allow-injections are wired in ../opencode-append.jsonc.
# See `/harness` for the full recipe.
